rComments: Careless, disorganised, doesn't know how to teach.

Professor Mohamed Mansour is enthusiastic at the topics taught, and offers extra assistance after class. He provided structured sample code slide in Binary Tree lecture; I benefited from him working through deleting tree nodes after class. His slides serve as useful resource for course review. Mansour has a good temper, a fun and friendly person.
Extremely disorganized and clearly does not care about teaching the course. Hired a bunch of guest lecturers, one of whom didn't even show up. Only good thing was that the class was super easy.

Literally worst instructor I have ever had. Incredibly disorganized and did not bother to communicate with students at all. Turned what was supposed to be an interesting if mandatory course into a huge pain. The only good side to this course was that pretty much everyone got an A.
